description: XNXX, a site with 45 million users, is now a VLOP under the EU's Digital Services Act (DSA). Compliance by mid-November 2024 involves age-verification, public data access, ad repository, user protection, and risk assessments. The site exceeded the DSA threshold, risking fines up to 6% of its revenue. Total VLOPSE count stands at 25.

Afridi highlighted that Babar has had ample opportunities, leading the team in multiple World Cups and Asia Cups. He suggested a permanent change in leadership to allow new captains full time to develop.

description: Train traffic on the Konkan Railway route was paralysed once again on Wednesday morning due to severe water-logging inside a tunnel at Pernem in Goa, leading to the cancellation and diversion of several trains and stranding passengers at various stations. Goa has been receiving heavy rains for the last three days. The train disruption began at 2:35 pm on Tuesday when water began oozing into the Pernem tunnel between the Madure-Pernem section, according to Konkan Railway Corporation (KRCL) Deputy General Manager Baban Ghatge.
title: Watch: Water seeps into Goa tunnel, train services disrupted

description: Captain Shubman Gill struck a fluent half-century as India claimed a 23-run win over hosts Zimbabwe in the third T20 international in Harare on Wednesday to take a 2-1 lead in the five-match series. A youthful India side without several members of their victorious World Cup squad elected to bat and posted 182 for four in their 20 overs, before Zimbabwe overcame a dismal start to reach 159 for six thanks to an unbeaten 65 from 49 balls by Dion Myers.
title: 3rd T20I: India beat Zimbabwe for 2-1 series lead

description: The Dalai Lama's advanced age and health issues have raised concerns among Tibetan exiles about the future of their movement and leadership. China's intention to control the selection of his successor adds to these concerns, highlighting the political and cultural uncertainties faced by Tibetans both in exile and in Tibet. The Dalai Lama, whose real name is Tenzin Gyatso, has been a central figure in the Tibetan struggle for autonomy and cultural preservation since assuming his role as the 14th Dalai Lama in 1950.
title: Tibetan dilemma: Uncertain future without the Dalai Lama

description: President Vladimir Putin is experiencing a surge in diplomatic activity both domestically and internationally, challenging efforts by the US and its allies to isolate him due to Russia's invasion of Ukraine. Since beginning his fifth presidential term in May, Putin has held over 20 meetings with leaders from various regions, including Europe, Asia, Africa, Latin America, and the Middle East. He has also made six international trips, despite an arrest warrant issued against him by the International Criminal Court for alleged war crimes in Ukraine.
title: First Xi, now PM Modi: How global 'outcast' Putin is on a diplomatic roll

description: With 188 Test matches under his belt, seasoned England fast bowler James Anderson stands second on the list of players with the most appearances, after Tendulkar (200) in the longest format of the game. With an impressive tally of 700 wickets from 187 matches, Anderson currently holds the third spot on the list of highest wicket-takers in Test history. This final match also presents him with an opportunity to surpass legendary spinner Shane Warne's record of 708 wickets.
title: Anderson names the best batter he has bowled against, and he is from India. Watch

description: At Galaxy Unpacked in Paris, Samsung launched the Galaxy Z Fold6, Z Flip6, Watch Ultra, smart ring (heart rate alerts, 10ATM water resistance, sleep analysis), Watch7 (FDA-approved), Galaxy Buds3 (interpreter tool). Featuring advanced technology like Snapdragon 8 Gen 3 and improved battery life, these devices highlight Samsung's innovation.

description: Prague Zoo has welcomed a second critically endangered Chinese pangolin within two years. The female pangolin, born on July 1st, is thriving under zoo care and could reach 250 grams this week. The breeding success is a significant milestone for the zoo's conservation efforts. Initially aimed at ensuring their survival and well being, zoo director Miroslav Bobek expressed amazement at the unexpected birth of two pangolin offspring within such a short timeframe. Breeding them in captivity is challenging, requiring specialised diets and precise environmental conditions.
title: Prague zoo celebrates rare birth of Chinese Pangolin

description: Railway Minister Ashwini Vaishnaw said loco pilots are important members of the railway family and alleged that there is lot of misinformation and theatrics by the opposition to demotivate them. Vaishnaw took to X to highlight various steps taken by the Railways to improve the working condition of train drivers. "Duty hours of loco pilots are carefully monitored. Rest is provided meticulously after trips. The average duty hours are maintained within prescribed hours," he wrote.
title: 'Let me make it clear … ': Rly minister slams Rahul's claims on loco pilots

description: Nikolas Cruz, Parkland high school shooter, agreed to donate his brain for research in a settlement with a victim Anthony Borges. "I figured if scientists studied his brain they might be able to figure out what created this monster," said Borges' lawyer Alex Arreaza in a statement to Fox News Digital. "The settlement also Includes $430,000, media rights, profit restrictions. Previously, Broward Schools paid $26M, including $1.25M for Borges.
title: 'Unique settlement': US mass shooter to donate brain for science

description: Gautam Gambhir's primary focus at the moment is assembling a support staff that aligns with his vision, as he prepares to tackle the immense challenges that lie ahead during his three-year tenure as India's head coach. The financial details surrounding his appointment are yet to be finalized, but Gambhir considers that to be the "last of his concerns" at this juncture. It is understood that Gambhir will be provided with his own team to work with, who will also closely coordinate with the NCA coaches. The coaches oversee the pathways teams (India A and U-19) as well as targeted players.

description: After Rohit Sharma stepped down from T20I cricket following a victorious ICC T20 World Cup campaign, it is expected that all-rounder Hardik Pandya will take over as captain of the Indian team in the shortest format. Concurrently, sources indicate that wicketkeeper-batter KL Rahul is set to assume leadership responsibilities in ODIs. The decision comes as the Indian team looks to transition to a new era of leadership, with Rohit's tenure as captain coming to an end. The move is expected to provide opportunities for the next generation of players to step up and take on greater roles within the team.

description: Mihir Shah, the prime suspect in the Mumbai BMW hit-and-run, has been remanded to police custody. Mihir, who is the son of Shiv Sena leader Rajesh Shah, had been absconding since July 7 when he rammed his BMW into a two-wheeler, resulting in the death of 45-year-old Kaveri Nakhwa, who was riding pillion, while her husband Pradeep survived with injuries.
title: Hit-and-run: Mihir sent to police custody till July 16, 'need to find who helped him', cops tell court

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi's visit to Austria at the beginning of his third term focuses on discussions with Chancellor Karl Nehammer. They address global disputes, condemn terrorism, and highlight the long-standing India-Austria relationship. Talks also cover the Ukraine conflict and Middle East situation, reflecting the complex geopolitical landscape. "I have said it earlier also that this is not the time for war," reiterated PM Modi in Austria. He made similar remarks in the presence of Russian President Vladimir Putin in Moscow on Tuesday.

description: Sunil Gavaskar, now 75, received tributes from Pakistani legends for his influence on Virat Kohli, Sachin Tendulkar, and role in the 1977 series. Called the 'original batting don,' he significantly contributed to cricket in Sharjah and remains a notable commentator, admired alongside contemporaries like Bishen Singh Bedi. In addition to being a superb batsman, Miandad claimed that Gavaskar was also a good man. The two had played many matches against each other on the field.

description: The US, Canada, and the Netherlands collaborated to dismantle a Russian propaganda operation using AI-generated fake social media accounts. The operation aimed to spread misinformation about the Ukraine war. Two domains were seized, and nearly 1,000 fake accounts were disrupted. Authorities warn of ongoing efforts to influence elections.

description: Heavy rains in Uttarakhand caused landslides, blocking Badrinath Highway near Patalganga Langsi Tunnel, Yamunotri Highway at Pagal Nala, trapping many. description: Traffic on Delhi-Meerut Expressway in Ghaziabad to face disruptions as police close down six lanes for kanwar yatra. Authorities preparing traffic diversion plan for the closure from July 28 night. Last year, diversions led to traffic jams on NH-9. Pilgrims have multiple routes to reach Haridwar with most using Pipeline Road, DME, or NH-34. Diversions planned to accommodate kanwariyas while ensuring other vehicles are redirected. Stay informed via social media for diversion updates.

description: AIIMS Jodhpur suspended Hukmaram Godara, a missing MBBS student, for impersonating Raj Pandey in NEET at DAV School, Muzaffarpur. Bihar police's investigation revealed Godara was paid Rs 4 lakh and caught during biometric checks but released with an apology. The exam centre administration is also under scrutiny. AIIMS confirmed Bihar police requested information. Godara, missing since May 2 and absent from a recent exam, remains unfound despite police efforts.
title: AIIMS Jodhpur student suspended for appearing as dummy in NEET

description: Maharashtra CM Eknath Shinde-led Shiv Sena sacked Rajesh Shah, father of Worli hit-and-run accused Mihir Shah, as deputy leader. Rajesh was arrested for destroying evidence and later bailed. The accident killed Kaveri Nakhwa. Shiv Sena MLA Aaditya Thackeray demands Mihir be tried for murder, criticizing the delay in his arrest and alleging police lapses.

description: A bus and milk tanker crash on Agra-Lucknow expressway in Unnao district results in 18 fatalities and 19 injuries. description: The aftermath of the ambush in Kathua revealed a scene of fierce resistance by the soldiers: bloodstains on the road, helmets, bullet shells, vehicles with shattered windscreens, and flattened tires. Four Seasons and Trident Bandra Kurla raised rates, with Trident fully booked. ITC Grand Central charges Rs 25,370. description: Gypsy Rose Blanchard, who was imprisoned for recruiting her boyfriend to kill her mother Clauddine “Dee Dee” Blanchard, has announced her pregnancy just over a year after her release. In a YouTube video, the 32-year-old expressed her excitement about becoming a mother and her desire to be everything her mother wasn’t. The case gained attention for its disturbing details of Dee Dee’s abuse and Munchausen syndrome by proxy. Since her release, Blanchard has promoted a Lifetime docuseries and e-book about her experiences.

description: Lisa Pisano, 54, from New Jersey, passed away after living 47 days with a genetically modified pig kidney transplant. She was critically ill with kidney and heart failure. The transplant failed due to inadequate blood flow from a mechanical heart pump. Despite the setback, her case advanced xenotransplantation, offering hope to those in need of alternative organ supplies.

description: The UP govt has waived registration tax on hybrid cars to promote eco-friendly transport by aligning their costs with petrol cars. Effective July 1, it covers various types as noted by Manoj Kumar Singh to NIC. Hybrids, combining combustion engines and electric motors, are more fuel-efficient. PK Singh emphasized the state's green effort. The new models like Toyota Innova HyCross should see increased sales. Tariq Jafri from Toyota Espirit expects significant sales boosts due to the Rs 2-3 lakh price drop. Three showrooms in Noida, Greater Noida anticipate increased sales.
